ary )                                                                                                           ?NUMBER ( a -- n T | F )                                -       ?NUMBER ( a -- d T | F )                         DOUBLE -       "question-number"                                               Attempt to convert the string at A+1 to a signed number.        Return its value and T if the conversion succeeds, otherwise    return false. The first character of the string may be a minus  sign, which negates the value of the resulting number. The      digits of the number are converted by CONVERT with respect to   the current BASE. The first character after the digits in the   string must be a blank character.                               When the double word set is loaded, ?NUMBER will return a       double-size number D in case of success.                        Example: : FOO $" 123 " ?NUMBER ;  \ gives 123 1                                                                                ( T3XFORTH Glossary )                                                                                                           ?SAME ( a1 a2 -- f )  Code                              -       "question-same"                                                 Return truth when the packed string at A1 matches the           dictionary entry at A2. Note: the dictionary entry will be      in a special format, so swapping the arguments of ?SAME will    cause an undefined result. Characters of A1 must be in upper    case.                                                           : FOO $" DUP" ['] DUP >NFA ?SAME ;  \ gives -1                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  