ompile words and literals to the dictionary     instead of executing them. Words flagged IMMEDIATE (q.v.) will  be executed during compilation, words flagged COMPILE-ONLY will cause an error while interpreting. Interpretation or compilationends, when there are no more words in the input buffer. For     details See >IN, #TIB, and BLK.                                 Example: : FOO QUERY INTERPRET ;  \ a FORTH interpreter                                                                         ( T3XFORTH Glossary )                                                                                                           INVERT ( w -- w )                                       EFORTH  "invert"                                                        Flip all bits in the machine word W.                            Example: [HEX] FFFF INVERT  \ gives 0                                                                                           IS ( -- )                                               -       "is"                                                            Usage: DEFER name ... definition IS name -- Modify the          deferred word NAME so that its execution will cause the         previously defined word to be invoked. See DEFER.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               ( T3XFORTH Glossary )                                                                                                           J  ( -- w )                                             SF      "j"                                                             Usage: in DO loops. Return the current loop index of an outer   DO loop, i.e. the index of a DO loop in which the current DO    loop is embedded.                                               Example:                        