he user.                                                                        TMP ( -- a )          VARIABLE                          -       "t-m-p"                                                         Temporary storage location of the system. Do not use.                                                                           ( T3XFORTH Glossary )                                                                                                           TX! ( c -- )          Code                              -       "t-x-store"                                                     Write the character C to the console device.                                                                                    TYPE ( a n -- )                                         F-79    "type:                                                          Print N characters starting at address A. When N<1, do nothing. Example: : FOO $" Hello!" COUNT TYPE ;  \ print Hello!                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          ( T3XFORTH Glossary )                                                                                                           U. ( u -- )                                             F-79    "u-dot"                                                         Print N as an unsigned number with respect to the current BASE, followed by one space character.                                Example: 50000 U.  \ print 50000 and a blank                                                                                    U.R ( u n -- )                                          EFORTH  "u-dot-r"                                                       