"                                               Divide the unsigned double word UD by U and return their        double-size floored quotient (UDQ) and single-size remainder    (modulo, UM). Unlike UM/MOD the operation cannot overflow       (unless U=0).                                                   Example: 1,234,567 10 UDM/MOD  \ gives 7 123,456                                                                                ( T3XFORTH Glossary )                                                                                                           UM* ( u1 u2 -- ud )                                     F-83    "u-m-star"                                                      Return the double-word product of U1 and U2.                    Example: 16386 16 UM*  \ gives 0 4                                                                                              UM+ ( u1 u2 -- ud )   Code                              EFORTH  "u-m-plus"                                                      Return the double-word sum of U1 and U2.                        Example: 32768 32768 UM+  \ gives 0 1                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           ( T3XFORTH Glossary )                                                                                                           UM/MOD ( ud u -- um uq )                                F-83    "u-m-slash-mod"                                                 Divide the unsigned double word UD by U and return their        floored quotient (UQ) and remainder (modulo, UM).               Example: 65,537 16 UM/MOD  \ gives -1 4096                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      ( T3XFORTH Glossary )                                                                                                           UNLOOP ( -- )                                           -       "unloop"                                                        Usage: DO ... UNLOOP EXIT ... LOOP -- Remove the index and      limit of a DO loop from the return stack, so that the word      using the loop can EXIT from within the loop. Also works with   +LOOP and /LOOP.                                                Example:                                                        : FOO 10 0 DO I 5 = IF UNLOOP EXIT THEN I. LOOP ;               \ print 0 1 2 3 4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               ( T3XFORTH Glossary )                                                                                                           UNTIL ( f -- )        IMMEDIATE COMPILE-ONLY            F-79    "until"                                                         Usage: BEGIN ... condition UNTIL -- Repeat execution of the     words between BEGIN and UNTIL until the given condition returns truth, then exit the loop. When the condition is false upon     entering the loop for the first time, the words 