E. When the condition is true,  execute the words between WHILE and REPEAT and then start over  at BEGIN. When the condition is false, leave the loop and       continue execution after REPEAT. When the condition is false    upon entering the loop for the first time, the words between    WHILE and REPEAT are never executed.                            Example:                                                        : FOO BEGIN KEY DUP 27 <> WHILE EMIT REPEAT ;                   \ echo keys until ESC is pressed                                                                                                                                                                ( T3XFORTH Glossary )                                                                                                           WIPE ( -- )                                             SF      "wipe"                                                          Wipe the currently active disk buffer by overwriting it with    blanks.                                                         Example: 999 BUFFER WIPE  \ allocate and wipe block 999                                                                         WITHIN ( u ul uh -- f )                                 EFORTH  "within"                                                        Return truth, if UL <= U < UH.                                  Example: 65 32 127 WITHIN  \ gives -1                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           ( T3XFORTH Glossary )                                                                                                           WORD ( c -- a )                                         F-79    "word"                                                          Extract letters from the current input buffer an